  "diary": "Started the day right with an early swim at Kirkland Community Pool—the water was perfect, cold enough to wake me up but not punishing. Commute to dispatch was smooth; I caught the news about the Light Rail closure but it didn't affect my route. Work was steady, the usual mix of calls. There was this moment around 10:30 when things got quiet, and I noticed the bars downtown had their doors open early for the USA-Wales match. Made me smile thinking about how a soccer game can shift a whole city's energy. Grabbed lunch at Café Veloce, their espresso hit different today. Afternoon shift flew by. Got home, made some decent pasta, then spent a couple hours with my notebook working through some verses about timing and distance. Friends came over for board games tonight—nothing fancy, just Catan and laughter. There's something grounding about a Monday that moves like this, purposeful but not frantic.",
